data.enText: to not include sth/sb, either deliberately or because you have forgotten it/them
If you are a student, you can omit questions 16–18.

data.chText: 人们感到惊讶，史密斯竟未列入该队。
data.enText: People were surprised that Smith was omitted from the team.
to not do or fail to do sth

data.chText: 她没说他们当晚要留宿的事。
data.enText: She omitted to mention that they were staying the night.

example: How could I miss that typo?
The workers on the conveyor belt miss one out of ten

tr: prevent from being included or considered or accepted
example: The bad results were excluded from the report

value.def: If you omit something, you do not include it in an activity or piece of work, deliberately or accidentally.

example.ex: Omit the salt in this recipe...
example.tran: 省略菜谱中放盐这一步。

example.ex: Our apologies to David Pannick for omitting his name from last week's article.
example.tran: 我们在上周的文章里漏掉了戴维·潘尼克的名字，特此向他致歉。

value.def: If you omit to do something, you do not do it.

example.ex: His new girlfriend had omitted to tell him she was married.
example.tran: 他的新女友未把自己已婚的事实告诉他。
